Program: Outlook
Title: India's forgotten workers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0104kv3
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 14 Nov 2012
Indian journalist, Aman Sethi makes friends with India's forgotten workers - the house-painters and builders who live from hand to mouth. We also meet the Turkish man who's using basketball to stop Kurdish youths from clashing with the security forces. And Matthew Bannister talks to Pablo Borboroglu, the marine biologist from Argentina who's fighting to save the world's penguins. A Free Man: A True Story of Life and Death in Delhi by Aman Sethi, Publisher Vintage/Random House India Image: Indian labourers work at a construction site Credit: AFP/Getty Show less